text.tspan: Comparison of median income (or consumption) in LIS and World Bank PIP, 1978 to 2013
This data is adjusted for inflation and for differences in the cost of living between countries.
Median income or expenditure per day (PIP)
Daily median equivalized disposable household income (LIS)
Data source: Incomes across the Distribution Database (Nolan, Thewissen, Roser) in levels (2016); World Bank PIP
Note: PIP data is measured in international-$ at 2017 prices. Depending on the country and year, it relates to either disposable income or consumption per capita. LIS
data in addition adjusts for the size and composition of households.
